<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="type material">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Holotype</emphasis>
♂ (SCAU G24), China, Guangdong Province, Yangjiang City, Yangchun, Cave Yanzi Dong, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="22" direction="north" minutes="5" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="22.083334">22°5'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="111" direction="east" minutes="36" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="50" value="111.613884">111°36'50&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 400 m alt., 2016-X-29, leg. Tian Mingyi, Chen Mengzhen &amp; Wang Dianmei. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Paratypes</emphasis>
: 2 ♂, 26 ♀ (SCAU G24), same data as the holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">To emphasise the metatergal anterior tubercles being very sharp and coniform.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
Differs from congeners of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1895" class="Diplopoda" family="Cambalopsidae" genus="Glyphiulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Glyphiulus formosus" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Glyphiulus formosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group by the conical shape of the anterior tubercles of metaterga and by the first segment of the telopodite being significantly enlarged in ♂ legs 1, combined with the anterior gonopod process being slender, finger-shaped and curved inwards distally. Based on molecular evidence, 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. conuliformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="conuliformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">G. conuliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. differs from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gervais" authorityYear="1847" class="Diplopoda" family="Cambalopsidae" genus="Glyphiulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Glyphiulus" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Glyphiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species analysed in a&gt; 17.0% uncorrected p-distance of the COI barcoding gene.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
Length ca. 32.5-37.0 (♂) or 47.0-58.0 mm (♀), mid-body rings round in cross-section, their width and height similar, 1.7-2.0 mm (♂) or 2.2-3.0 mm (♀). Body with 48-53 (♂) or 57-67 (♀) podous + 2-4 apodous rings + telson. Colouration dark brownish, head and legs yellowish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pictures of live animals A G. sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Niubi Yan B G. scutatus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Bianfu Dong C G. portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Baiyan Dong D G. xiniudong Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Xiniu Dong E G. conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Yanzi Dong." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705255" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">5E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Head</emphasis>
surface smooth. Labrum with four teeth anteromedially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head and collum B right antenna, oral view C gnathochilarium D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H penes I anterior gonopods, caudal view J, K posterior gonopods, frontal and caudal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E), 0.2 mm (F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705259" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">9C</figureCitation>
). Ocellaria blackish, with 12-22 ommatidia arranged in 2-3 irregular linear rows (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head and collum B right antenna, oral view C gnathochilarium D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H penes I anterior gonopods, caudal view J, K posterior gonopods, frontal and caudal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E), 0.2 mm (F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705259" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">9A</figureCitation>
). Antennae slender, slightly clavate, reaching back to middle of rings 2 and 3; in length, antennomeres 5&gt; 3&gt; 2 ≈ 4&gt; 6&gt; 1&gt; 7. Antennomeres 5-7 each with a distodorsal field or corolla of bacilliform sensilla (sensory bacilli). Antennomere 7 with four sensory cones (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head and collum B right antenna, oral view C gnathochilarium D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H penes I anterior gonopods, caudal view J, K posterior gonopods, frontal and caudal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E), 0.2 mm (F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705259" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">9B</figureCitation>
). Gnathochilarium with a separate promentum, polytrichous on promentum and mentum, lamellae linguales each with 6-7 setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head and collum B right antenna, oral view C gnathochilarium D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H penes I anterior gonopods, caudal view J, K posterior gonopods, frontal and caudal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E), 0.2 mm (F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705259" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">9C</figureCitation>
). Mandible not dissected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Collum</emphasis>
: crests complete and evident; carinotaxy formula I-III+P+M (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: ot: ozoporiferous tubercle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705258" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">8A, B</figureCitation>
). Following metaterga strongly crested, anterior tubercles very sharp and coniform; carinotaxy formula 2/2+I/i+3/3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: ot: ozoporiferous tubercle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705258" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">8</figureCitation>
). Ozoporiferous tubercles very large, coniform (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: ot: ozoporiferous tubercle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705258" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">8C, D</figureCitation>
). Tegument delicately alveolate-areolate, fine longitudinal striations in front of stricture. Rings 2 and 3 with long pleural flaps.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705258" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" start="Figure 8" startId="F8">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Figure 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Diplopoda" family="Cambalopsidae" genus="Glyphiulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Glyphiulus conuliformis" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conuliformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Glyphiulus conuliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">A, B</emphasis>
anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">C, D</emphasis>
mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">E, F</emphasis>
posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: ot: ozoporiferous tubercle.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Epiproct</emphasis>
simple, caudal edge with a very low central protrusion, dorsally with an obvious sharp tubercle (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: ot: ozoporiferous tubercle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705258" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">8E</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts regularly convex, each with several irregular rows of setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: ot: ozoporiferous tubercle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705258" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">8F</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct transversely bean-shaped, with 3+3 small setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Legs</emphasis>
slender, about 1.3 times as long as mid-body height; claw with a small accessory spine at base, about 1/6 as long as claw (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head and collum B right antenna, oral view C gnathochilarium D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H penes I anterior gonopods, caudal view J, K posterior gonopods, frontal and caudal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E), 0.2 mm (F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705259" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">9D</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 1 very strongly reduced, represented by a sternum showing a pair of small, unfused, paramedian, subunciform prongs directed forward, with about 4-5+4-5 long setae at base; flanked by strongly separated, rudimentary, 2-segmented, asymmetric leg vestiges, first segment significantly enlarged (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head and collum B right antenna, oral view C gnathochilarium D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H penes I anterior gonopods, caudal view J, K posterior gonopods, frontal and caudal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E), 0.2 mm (F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705259" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">9F</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 2 slightly hypertrophied, coxae large; penes rather small, much shorter than coxae, oblong-subtrapeziform, each with 1 or 2 strong setae distolaterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head and collum B right antenna, oral view C gnathochilarium D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H penes I anterior gonopods, caudal view J, K posterior gonopods, frontal and caudal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E), 0.2 mm (F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705259" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">9H</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 3 modified through coxae being especially slender and elongate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Glyphiulus conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head and collum B right antenna, oral view C gnathochilarium D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H penes I anterior gonopods, caudal view J, K posterior gonopods, frontal and caudal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E), 0.2 mm (F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705259" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">9E</figureCitation>
). ♂ femora 6 and 7 normal, without modifications.
</paragraph>
